#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:423
msgid ""
"Specifies the subsystem the error configuration will apply to, such as "
"metadata IO or memory allocation. Different subsystems will have different "
"error handlers for which behaviour can be configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:427
msgid "-error handlers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:428
msgid "Defines the behavior for a specific error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:430
msgid ""
"The filesystem behavior during an error can be set via ``sysfs`` files. Each "
"error handler works independently - the first condition met by an error "
"handler for a specific class will cause the error to be propagated rather "
"than reset and retried."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:435
msgid ""
"The action taken by the filesystem when the error is propagated is context "
"dependent - it may cause a shut down in the case of an unrecoverable error, "
"it may be reported back to userspace, or it may even be ignored because "
"there's nothing useful we can with the error or anyone we can report it to "
"(e.g. during unmount)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:441
msgid ""
"The configuration files are organized into the following hierarchy for each "
"mounted filesystem:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:444 ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:494
msgid "/sys/fs/xfs/<dev>/error/<class>/<error>/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:446
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:447
msgid "<dev>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:448
msgid ""
"The short device name of the mounted filesystem. This is the same device "
"name that shows up in XFS kernel error messages as \"XFS(<dev>): ...\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:451
msgid "<class>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:452
msgid ""
"The subsystem the error configuration belongs to. As of 4.9, the defined "
"classes are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:455
msgid "\"metadata\": applies metadata buffer write IO"
msgstr ""

