#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:574
msgid "Zoned Filesystems"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:576
msgid "For zoned file systems, the following attributes are exposed in:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:578
msgid "/sys/fs/xfs/<dev>/zoned/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:580
msgid ""
"max_open_zones                (Min:  1  Default:  Varies  Max:  UINTMAX)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:581
msgid ""
"This read-only attribute exposes the maximum number of open zones available "
"for data placement. The value is determined at mount time and is limited by "
"the capabilities of the backing zoned device, file system size and the "
"max_open_zones mount option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:586
msgid "zonegc_low_space              (Min:  0  Default:  0  Max:  100)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/xfs.rst:587
msgid ""
"Define a percentage for how much of the unused space that GC should keep "
"available for writing. A high value will reclaim more of the space occupied "
"by unused blocks, creating a larger buffer against write bursts at the cost "
"of increased write amplification.  Regardless of this value, garbage "
"collection will always aim to free a minimum amount of blocks to keep "
"max_open_zones open for data placement purposes."
msgstr ""
